---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LibraryIndex from '../components/LibraryIndex.astro';
import RoleNavigator from '../components/RoleNavigator.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Law library" description="Dealership pay-plan and wage-and-hour issue guides with primary public sources.">
  <main id="main-content">
    <header class="library-hero shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">California + federal · primary sources linked</p>
      <h1>Open the law library.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Choose a dealership role or move directly to an issue. Every article keeps its scope, review date, and primary sources in view.</p>
    </header>
    <section class="shell section section--ruled">
      <div class="section-heading"><div><p class="eyebrow">By pay plan</p><h2>Who is being paid?</h2></div><p>Role labels are a starting point. Actual duties and pay mechanics still matter.</p></div>
      <RoleNavigator />
    </section>
    <section class="section section--mist"><div class="shell"><div class="section-heading"><div><p class="eyebrow">By issue</p><h2>What is the collision point?</h2></div><p>Use issue pages to inspect one legal problem across multiple dealership roles.</p></div><LibraryIndex /></div></section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .library-hero { padding-block: var(--space-9); }
  .library-hero h1 { max-width: 60rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
</style>
